Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ricardo Alarcon de Quesada, President of the Cuban 
National Assembly of the People's Government, today held talks 
with (Andre Santini), head of the group of French deputies, 
Friends of the Island, whom he briefed on the current situation 
in Cuba. 
  During his stay in Paris, Alarcon intends to meet with his 
French counterpart (Phillipe Sagan), with Senate President (Rene 
Moroni), and with Robert Hue, national secretary of the French 
Communist Party, among other personalities. 
  Alarcon de Quesada arrived in Paris this weekend on the 
third 
leg of his tour through Europe that began 15 days ago in 
Brussels. In the meetings held with congressmen, government 
officials, politicians, and businessmen from Germany and 
Belgium, a spirit of interest and responsiveness has prevailed, 
Cuban delegation sources reported. 

